1
00:00:00,687 --> 00:00:03,086
(The last day of January, 2026, has already come.)

2
00:00:03,087 --> 00:00:04,326
Oh, my. Seriously...

3
00:00:04,327 --> 00:00:05,327
- Hey, Shin Dong!
- I like...

4
00:00:05,328 --> 00:00:07,396
- Oh, hey, Hee Chul.
- What?

5
00:00:07,421 --> 00:00:08,458
Why? What is it?

6
00:00:08,762 --> 00:00:10,091
- Is Shin Dong absent today?
- He didn't come.

7
00:00:10,092 --> 00:00:12,131
- Shin Dong didn't come.
- His desk is gone too.

8
00:00:12,132 --> 00:00:13,161
- His desk is gone?
- It's gone.

9
00:00:13,162 --> 00:00:14,901
- For almost a month, I...
- Be quiet.

10
00:00:14,902 --> 00:00:16,001
Watch your head.

11
00:00:16,002 --> 00:00:17,832
Be careful. You might hit your head.

12
00:00:18,015 --> 00:00:19,080
Be quiet.

13
00:00:19,292 --> 00:00:21,610
- Why come through the front door?
- Listen up.

14
00:00:22,069 --> 00:00:25,839
Hee Chul and Shin Dong traveled across the world...

15
00:00:25,864 --> 00:00:28,245
- for their world tour concert.
- That's right.

16
00:00:28,331 --> 00:00:31,191
Surprisingly, Hee Chul...

17
00:00:31,929 --> 00:00:32,989
seems fine.

18
00:00:33,429 --> 00:00:37,599
But Shin Dong... He's a bit frail, you know.

19
00:00:38,099 --> 00:00:39,598
- So...
- It may be surprising to you.

20
00:00:39,599 --> 00:00:40,968
But I'm naturally vigorous...

21
00:00:40,969 --> 00:00:42,438
while Shin Dong is a bit frail.

22
00:00:42,439 --> 00:00:44,498
He's not feeling well,

23
00:00:44,499 --> 00:00:46,969
so he decided to take a few weeks off of school.

24
00:00:47,139 --> 00:00:48,738
(Worried)

25
00:00:48,739 --> 00:00:51,078
So today, for Shin Dong,

26
00:00:51,079 --> 00:00:55,249
let's each write down cheerful words.

27
00:00:55,379 --> 00:00:57,418
Shin Dong seemed mentally weaker than I thought.

28
00:00:57,419 --> 00:00:59,648
- That's right.
- Yeong Cheol must be thinking,

29
00:00:59,649 --> 00:01:02,188
"I wish Shin Dong were here and Hee Chul were sick."

30
00:01:02,189 --> 00:01:04,558
That's not true. Why would you say such a thing?

31
00:01:04,559 --> 00:01:06,188
- He must be out of his mind.
- I'd never be absent from school.

32
00:01:06,189 --> 00:01:07,759
- I would never think that way.
- I'd never be absent from school.

33
00:01:07,989 --> 00:01:09,828
You didn't share a green room with Shin Dong, did you?

34
00:01:09,829 --> 00:01:10,829
We used to share a green room,

35
00:01:10,830 --> 00:01:12,299
but Shin Dong got stressed out. So we used separate rooms.

36
00:01:13,129 --> 00:01:14,769
He's my partner.

37
00:01:15,239 --> 00:01:16,568
I feel like he's sick because of me.

38
00:01:16,569 --> 00:01:18,408
So write, "Please just come back."

39
00:01:18,409 --> 00:01:19,608
"Please come back to me."

40
00:01:19,609 --> 00:01:22,308
- "I won't share a room with you."
- I want to say, "Shin Dong..."

41
00:01:22,309 --> 00:01:23,908
- Jang Hoon, go ahead.
- Write, "Shin Dong,"

42
00:01:23,909 --> 00:01:26,379
"eat a lot and regain your weight before you come back."

43
00:01:27,249 --> 00:01:28,348
(Come back)

44
00:01:28,349 --> 00:01:30,248
(Get fat and come back)

45
00:01:30,249 --> 00:01:31,788
- You little...
- Change his comment.

46
00:01:31,789 --> 00:01:32,818
"I will soon..."

47
00:01:32,819 --> 00:01:34,318
"I will soon follow you."

48
00:01:34,319 --> 00:01:36,259
You just can't seem to improve.

49
00:01:37,359 --> 00:01:38,928
Sir, please teach me.

50
00:01:38,929 --> 00:01:41,088
- What can I do to become funnier?
- Yeong Cheol...

51
00:01:41,089 --> 00:01:42,999
I'll make an acrostic poem with "Shin Dong."

52
00:01:43,229 --> 00:01:44,558
- Okay. Go ahead.
- Shin.

53
00:01:44,559 --> 00:01:45,998
- On exciting Saturdays...
- On Saturdays...

54
00:01:45,999 --> 00:01:48,168
Dong. We need Shin Dong.

55
00:01:48,169 --> 00:01:50,698
Shin Dong, I hope you come back soon.

56
00:01:50,699 --> 00:01:52,568
- This is...
- He can't seem to improve.

57
00:01:52,569 --> 00:01:53,808
- This is...
- Exactly.

58
00:01:53,809 --> 00:01:55,478
- He can't seem to improve.
- the Grand Award winner's grace.

59
00:01:55,479 --> 00:01:56,838
- The Grand Award winner's grace.
- What? It was good.

60
00:01:56,839 --> 00:01:59,148
- "While taking time off,"
- You can't do it by trying.

61
00:01:59,149 --> 00:02:01,578
"I hope Shin Dong dates someone too."

62
00:02:01,579 --> 00:02:02,948
"The second period without Shin Dong..."

63
00:02:02,949 --> 00:02:04,318
- "is meaningless."
- That's right.

64
00:02:04,319 --> 00:02:05,488
Oh, my. These are nice.

65
00:02:05,489 --> 00:02:08,318
If Shin Dong watches this, he'll come back soon.

66
00:02:08,319 --> 00:02:10,188
So many people hope for it.

67
00:02:10,189 --> 00:02:11,558
Who will lead us in the second period?

68
00:02:11,559 --> 00:02:12,658
The classroom feels empty without him.

69
00:02:12,659 --> 00:02:14,388
I want Ho Dong to host the second part...

70
00:02:14,389 --> 00:02:16,099
like he did "Star King."

71
00:02:17,899 --> 00:02:18,869
- Gosh, that startled me.
- Hey.

72
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:20,068
Oh, my. What's going on?

73
00:02:20,069 --> 00:02:21,498
Gi Seong has lost so much weight.

74
00:02:21,499 --> 00:02:22,499
- I thought he was Shin Dong.
- Exactly.

75
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:25,368
(Don't be cowardly, having fun)

76
00:02:25,369 --> 00:02:26,838
Without us. Let us join you.

77
00:02:26,839 --> 00:02:27,938
- Oh, my. Jadu is here.
- All right?

78
00:02:27,939 --> 00:02:29,208
- Please come in.
- Hi.

79
00:02:29,209 --> 00:02:31,009
- Jadu is here.
- Hey, Jadu.

80
00:02:31,179 --> 00:02:32,448
(Another person comes in later as if he were the star of the day.)

81
00:02:32,449 --> 00:02:34,048
- Please come in.
- Jang Hoon! Oh, my.

82
00:02:34,049 --> 00:02:35,878
- We have such special guests today.
- I mean...

83
00:02:35,879 --> 00:02:37,219
- It's been such a long time.
- He looks like an idol star.

84
00:02:37,379 --> 00:02:38,788
- What kind of combination is this?
- The three of them...

85
00:02:38,789 --> 00:02:41,049
- came here together?
- Are you wearing makeup or what?

86
00:02:41,449 --> 00:02:42,918
- Jang Hoon.
- Let us introduce ourselves.

87
00:02:42,919 --> 00:02:44,188
Jang Hoon, you can sit down later.

88
00:02:44,189 --> 00:02:45,389
You should introduce yourself first.

89
00:02:45,989 --> 00:02:48,859
By the way, which school did you transfer from?

90
00:02:48,899 --> 00:02:52,099
We're from Warriors Of Resilience High School.

91
00:02:52,299 --> 00:02:54,268
I am... Roll it well

92
00:02:54,269 --> 00:02:56,338
I am Jadu, the gimbaptainer who needs to talk.

93
00:02:56,339 --> 00:02:58,569
- Jadu!
- Gimbaptainer.

94
00:02:58,739 --> 00:02:59,839
Hi.

95
00:03:00,169 --> 00:03:01,569
Being cowardly, I walk along the quayside,

96
00:03:02,109 --> 00:03:04,808
the place that smells fishy. I'm Gi Seong.

97
00:03:04,809 --> 00:03:05,948
- Bae Gi Seong!
- Bae Gi Seong.

98
00:03:05,949 --> 00:03:07,479
("Spring will come to me," Bae Gi Seong)

99
00:03:07,609 --> 00:03:08,749
The "KPop Demon Hunters" style makeup.

100
00:03:09,049 --> 00:03:11,278
- Seup Teun Hoon is here.
- "KPop Demon Hunters."

101
00:03:11,279 --> 00:03:12,288
- I am...
- Seup Teun Hoon.

102
00:03:12,289 --> 00:03:13,488
I transferred to another school...

103
00:03:13,489 --> 00:03:14,588
from Warriors Of Resilience High School.

104
00:03:14,589 --> 00:03:16,619
- Where...
- I'm from another school.

105
00:03:16,859 --> 00:03:18,358
I'm from Financial Struggle High School.

106
00:03:18,359 --> 00:03:19,359
Financial Struggle High School?

107
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,658
("Kim Jang Hoon Behind On Rent Due To Financial Struggle")

108
00:03:20,659 --> 00:03:22,159
(Sigh of compassion)

109
00:03:22,399 --> 00:03:23,828
He practiced that line for 30 minutes.

110
00:03:23,829 --> 00:03:25,828
- Gosh. Why didn't you guys laugh?
- The opening...

111
00:03:25,829 --> 00:03:27,768
The opening kick! Start over again.

112
00:03:27,769 --> 00:03:29,338
- Why didn't it make you laugh?
- "Financial Struggle High School."

113
00:03:29,339 --> 00:03:31,198
- We'll laugh this time.
- Do the opening again.

114
00:03:31,199 --> 00:03:33,268
You see, he practiced that line for the opening...

115
00:03:33,269 --> 00:03:35,538
- for 30 minutes.
- It took me a week...

116
00:03:35,539 --> 00:03:36,908
- You should've said it cheerfully.
- He practiced hard.

117
00:03:36,909 --> 00:03:38,308
- And loudly.
- "Financial Struggle High School."

118
00:03:38,309 --> 00:03:40,478
- I thought it was...
- How could he say that cheerfully?

119
00:03:40,479 --> 00:03:42,478
- You should've said it loudly.
- Self-Reflection High School.

120
00:03:42,479 --> 00:03:44,148
- Wasn't it?
- I transferred from that school...

121
00:03:44,149 --> 00:03:46,018
- to Financial Struggle High School.
- From Self-Reflection High School,

122
00:03:46,019 --> 00:03:47,188
you moved to Financial Struggle High School.

123
00:03:47,189 --> 00:03:49,388
Whichever school you went to before you came here,

124
00:03:49,389 --> 00:03:50,889
we sincerely welcome you!

125
00:03:51,189 --> 00:03:52,488
It's nice to meet you all.

126
00:03:52,489 --> 00:03:54,328
To be honest, I'm a little upset with you guys.

127
00:03:54,329 --> 00:03:56,958
None of you has come on the show before.

128
00:03:56,959 --> 00:03:58,158
- They've never come here before.
- That's because...

129
00:03:58,159 --> 00:04:00,228
- We weren't invited.
- Exactly.

130
00:04:00,229 --> 00:04:02,839
Gi Seong, did all the fat you lost go to your nose?

131
00:04:04,299 --> 00:04:06,038
He's wearing toy glasses with a fake nose.

132
00:04:06,039 --> 00:04:07,168
His nose remains the same.

133
00:04:07,169 --> 00:04:08,169
- He's wearing disguise glasses.
- Is that a fake nose?

134
00:04:08,170 --> 00:04:09,908
- It's weird that I lost weight, - Only the nose...

135
00:04:09,909 --> 00:04:11,808
- but the nose remained the same.
- Only the nose hasn't changed.

136
00:04:11,809 --> 00:04:13,348
When I upload a video,

137
00:04:13,349 --> 00:04:15,178
people ask me if I use a convex lens.

138
00:04:15,179 --> 00:04:16,518
- Right.
- Your nose...

139
00:04:16,519 --> 00:04:18,948
I use a normal lens, but it looks as if I used a convex lens.

140
00:04:18,949 --> 00:04:21,758
- My nose didn't get thinner.
- I'm worried about today's shoot.

141
00:04:21,759 --> 00:04:22,759
- Why?
- Why?

142
00:04:23,089 --> 00:04:24,589
- Why?
- You guys will...

143
00:04:25,429 --> 00:04:27,658
- call him "Jang Hoon" as well.
- Exactly.

144
00:04:27,659 --> 00:04:29,599
Jang Hoon, are you divorced?

145
00:04:30,759 --> 00:04:31,999
Sometimes I see news articles that say I'm divorced.

146
00:04:32,799 --> 00:04:35,068
My mom would read the article and call me...

147
00:04:35,069 --> 00:04:37,098
- to ask if I got married.
- That's funny.

148
00:04:37,099 --> 00:04:39,239
It turns out that the reporter wrote his family name "Kim."

149
00:04:39,809 --> 00:04:41,168
Then I would wonder if I really got married.

150
00:04:41,169 --> 00:04:42,438
- It's a true story.
- But...

151
00:04:42,439 --> 00:04:43,778
- Even you're confused?
- Really.

152
00:04:43,779 --> 00:04:44,908
- I read this news article...
- Yes?

153
00:04:44,909 --> 00:04:48,479
that said I had attended some kind of festival.

154
00:04:49,079 --> 00:04:52,388
I was like, "What festival?"

155
00:04:52,389 --> 00:04:54,118
"Seo Jang Hoon With 50 Million Dollars..."

156
00:04:54,119 --> 00:04:56,089
- "Struggling Financially."
- Exactly.

157
00:04:56,289 --> 00:04:58,628
I've never been a basketball player before.

158
00:04:58,629 --> 00:05:00,689
- But they say I used to be.
- Right. You play go.

159
00:05:00,989 --> 00:05:03,128
- Gi Seong, who did you want to see?
- They have different family names.

160
00:05:03,129 --> 00:05:06,328
I want to show my gratitude to one of you.

161
00:05:06,329 --> 00:05:07,668
I came here to see Ho Dong.

162
00:05:07,669 --> 00:05:09,838
- He must've been on "Star King."
- That can't be true.

163
00:05:09,839 --> 00:05:11,468
- The old-fashioned mindset.
- There are...

164
00:05:11,469 --> 00:05:13,638
bad rumors about Ho Dong, you know.

165
00:05:13,639 --> 00:05:15,008
- But...
- That he beat someone up?

166
00:05:15,009 --> 00:05:16,078
Things like that.

167
00:05:16,079 --> 00:05:17,878
But I was very grateful toward him...

168
00:05:17,879 --> 00:05:19,778
when I appeared on "Star King."

169
00:05:19,779 --> 00:05:20,779
It's "Star King" again.

170
00:05:20,780 --> 00:05:22,978
- The shoot went on for so long.
- Right.

171
00:05:22,979 --> 00:05:25,048
Whenever we had a break,

172
00:05:25,049 --> 00:05:27,089
Ho Dong called me.

173
00:05:27,889 --> 00:05:29,058
I was told to go to his green room.

174
00:05:29,059 --> 00:05:30,358
- Me?
- Yes. So I went there.

175
00:05:30,359 --> 00:05:31,789
- I was completely daunted.
- Right.

176
00:05:31,959 --> 00:05:33,228
But he said, "It's hard, right?"

177
00:05:33,229 --> 00:05:35,258
"It's hard to do a shoot that goes on for long."

178
00:05:35,259 --> 00:05:37,529
He was eating some packed food.

179
00:05:37,899 --> 00:05:39,728
- He offered me some food.
- He shared food?

180
00:05:39,729 --> 00:05:40,729
- It's a heartwarming story.
- He offered to share the food.

181
00:05:40,730 --> 00:05:42,238
- Had the food gone bad?
- I gave you food?

182
00:05:42,239 --> 00:05:43,698
- You gave me food.
- It must've gone bad.

183
00:05:43,699 --> 00:05:44,898
And then Ho Dong said,

184
00:05:44,899 --> 00:05:47,568
"This experience will help you last long in this industry."

185
00:05:47,569 --> 00:05:49,808
"If you endure the hard times and hold out,"

186
00:05:49,809 --> 00:05:52,348
"you will eventually become successful."

187
00:05:52,349 --> 00:05:53,508
- "So do your best."
- He made such a long comment?

188
00:05:53,509 --> 00:05:54,778
- What he said...
- No way. I think...

189
00:05:54,779 --> 00:05:56,218
- you two get the story straight.
- No.

190
00:05:56,219 --> 00:05:58,118
- I haven't met him in a long time.
- Ho Dong does it when necessary.

191
00:05:58,119 --> 00:05:59,748
After that, I forgot about it.

192
00:05:59,749 --> 00:06:01,888
But strangely, whenever I had a hard time,

193
00:06:01,889 --> 00:06:03,089
I thought of Ho Dong.

194
00:06:03,789 --> 00:06:05,658
He didn't help you out? You just thought of him?

195
00:06:05,659 --> 00:06:06,659
Because it was sincere advice.

196
00:06:06,660 --> 00:06:08,288
Yes, it was sincere advice. I felt the sincerity.

197
00:06:08,289 --> 00:06:10,998
Try to remember what really happened.

198
00:06:10,999 --> 00:06:13,668
I don't think I called you to my green room.

199
00:06:13,669 --> 00:06:16,238
Maybe I went to your green room with the food.

200
00:06:16,239 --> 00:06:18,568
- No, you weren't that kind.
- I see.

201
00:06:18,569 --> 00:06:20,068
- You always had the one...
- He wasn't that kind.

202
00:06:20,069 --> 00:06:21,568
who came to see you first...

203
00:06:21,569 --> 00:06:23,108
- tell the next one to come.
- That's right.

204
00:06:23,109 --> 00:06:24,808
Let's say Hee Chul just talked to Ho Dong.

205
00:06:24,809 --> 00:06:26,608
- Hey, Ho Dong wants to see you.
- Yes?

206
00:06:26,609 --> 00:06:28,378
- Oh, gosh. What do I do?
- Exactly.

207
00:06:28,379 --> 00:06:30,518
- That's right.
- What did he say? Did he hit you?

208
00:06:30,519 --> 00:06:32,148
- What happened?
- I don't know. Go and find out.

209
00:06:32,149 --> 00:06:33,548
You guys are his juniors. But I'm his senior.

210
00:06:33,549 --> 00:06:34,988
"Jang Hoon, Ho Dong wants to see you."

211
00:06:34,989 --> 00:06:37,019
Then I would go to see Ho Dong right away.

212
00:06:37,619 --> 00:06:38,628
It's true.

213
00:06:38,629 --> 00:06:39,858
(The thought of what happened makes him feel resentful.)

214
00:06:39,859 --> 00:06:41,928
- Of course, he did.
- But...

215
00:06:41,929 --> 00:06:43,998
- I was going to scold you...
- Did I really...

216
00:06:43,999 --> 00:06:45,898
- He was going to scold Ho Dong.
- You were going to scold him?

217
00:06:45,899 --> 00:06:47,198
- Did you not find the right time?
- How could you have done it?

218
00:06:47,199 --> 00:06:48,468
- You haven't scolded him yet?
- I have a similar story.

219
00:06:48,469 --> 00:06:50,538
As I said, Ho Dong really called me to his green room.

220
00:06:50,539 --> 00:06:51,539
- He hit you.
- My gosh.

221
00:06:51,639 --> 00:06:53,138
When he started his career in the TV industry,

222
00:06:53,139 --> 00:06:54,639
I lied about my age.

223
00:06:55,169 --> 00:06:57,479
He thought we had a small age gap, so we were on a first-name basis.

224
00:06:58,179 --> 00:06:59,449
I told him I was born in 1968.

225
00:07:00,379 --> 00:07:01,508
I was actually born in 1963.

226
00:07:01,509 --> 00:07:02,878
- You were born in 1970, yes?
- Yes.

227
00:07:02,879 --> 00:07:04,578
- So it was a two-year age gap.
- You lied about it by many years.

228
00:07:04,579 --> 00:07:06,688
I think he wanted to treat me like a same age friend.

229
00:07:06,689 --> 00:07:08,388
Ho Dong started the conversation.

230
00:07:08,389 --> 00:07:10,418
While talking, we tried to intimidate each other.

231
00:07:10,419 --> 00:07:13,028
But when he reached out his hand to touch my hair,

232
00:07:13,029 --> 00:07:14,389
and I ducked like this.

233
00:07:15,129 --> 00:07:16,898
He had something on his hair,

234
00:07:16,899 --> 00:07:18,528
- so I was going to take it off.
- But I ducked.

235
00:07:18,529 --> 00:07:19,529
(Flinching)

236
00:07:20,899 --> 00:07:22,139
At that moment...

237
00:07:22,739 --> 00:07:24,939
- You already lost.
- In my entire life...

238
00:07:25,669 --> 00:07:26,909
Ho Dong looked at me...

239
00:07:27,809 --> 00:07:30,679
and turned around. But I felt more humiliated the next time I met him.

240
00:07:30,909 --> 00:07:32,848
He said, "Jang Hoon, I'll help you stand out."

241
00:07:32,849 --> 00:07:34,278
It was when I went on "X-Man."

242
00:07:34,279 --> 00:07:36,448
He said I could make people laugh by being pranked.

243
00:07:36,449 --> 00:07:38,789
Whenever he had a chance, he lifted me up.

244
00:07:39,249 --> 00:07:40,688
And then he threw me down on the floor like this...

245
00:07:40,689 --> 00:07:42,489
saying, "Jang Hoon, you should be the one to be pranked."

246
00:07:43,589 --> 00:07:44,958
He did that repeatedly.

247
00:07:44,959 --> 00:07:46,158
I told him to put me down.

248
00:07:46,159 --> 00:07:47,858
- My goodness. That's embarrassing.
- But...

249
00:07:47,859 --> 00:07:50,628
Jang Hoon and I hung out together a lot in the green room...

250
00:07:50,629 --> 00:07:53,228
- regardless of the show.
- That brat.

251
00:07:53,229 --> 00:07:56,138
- Gi Seong wanted to see Ho Dong.
- Yes.

252
00:07:56,139 --> 00:07:57,438
What about you, Jadu?

253
00:07:57,439 --> 00:08:00,208
I really wanted to see Ho Dong.

254
00:08:00,209 --> 00:08:02,908
I missed him as I hadn't seen him in a while.

255
00:08:02,909 --> 00:08:05,948
I also wanted to see Hee Chul.

256
00:08:05,949 --> 00:08:08,108
Her hairstyle... How she dyed her hair reminds me...

257
00:08:08,109 --> 00:08:09,678
If you go to a famous salon, you can see...

258
00:08:09,679 --> 00:08:10,918
- puppies with fur dyed like that.
- Right?

259
00:08:10,919 --> 00:08:12,248
Many people get the wrong idea.

260
00:08:12,249 --> 00:08:13,249
People ask me where I had my hair dyed.

261
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:14,788
Many people with a small dog dye their fur like that.

262
00:08:14,789 --> 00:08:16,118
I had my hair dyed at a beauty salon,

263
00:08:16,119 --> 00:08:17,119
but some people think a dog groomer did it.

264
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,358
- Many people get the wrong idea.
- Really?

265
00:08:18,359 --> 00:08:20,428
- We missed Jadu a lot too.
- Right.

266
00:08:20,429 --> 00:08:21,688
- Indeed.
- We heard her songs a lot.

267
00:08:21,689 --> 00:08:23,458
- All this time - Not long ago...

268
00:08:23,459 --> 00:08:25,498
Jadu appeared on "Sing Again 4..."

269
00:08:25,499 --> 00:08:26,499
- not long ago.
- That's right.

270
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:28,798
- I enjoyed your performances.
- Let's hear the details later on.

271
00:08:28,799 --> 00:08:30,439
- All right.
- Jang Hoon,

272
00:08:30,969 --> 00:08:31,969
why did you come here?

273
00:08:32,769 --> 00:08:34,668
- What?
- You must've had a reason.

274
00:08:34,669 --> 00:08:35,978
- I'm just asking.
- But...

275
00:08:35,979 --> 00:08:37,778
- Out of curiosity.
- He's annoyed.

276
00:08:37,779 --> 00:08:38,878
- Why?
- By the way, Jang Hoon.

277
00:08:38,879 --> 00:08:40,148
- Do what you want to do.
- I heard...

278
00:08:40,149 --> 00:08:44,018
you decided to come here to scold Hee Chul properly.

279
00:08:44,019 --> 00:08:45,948
We get along so well together.

280
00:08:45,949 --> 00:08:47,088
Did Hee Chul give you hard times?

281
00:08:47,089 --> 00:08:49,858
- No way. I love him so much.
- Yeong Cheol, quiet down.

282
00:08:49,859 --> 00:08:51,359
I, too, am a TV celebrity.

283
00:08:51,789 --> 00:08:52,959
You don't look like one.

284
00:08:54,489 --> 00:08:55,898
- You don't look like one.
- Right?

285
00:08:55,899 --> 00:08:57,629
I agree. I look more like an English teacher.

286
00:08:58,059 --> 00:08:59,069
Why?

287
00:08:59,329 --> 00:09:01,528
You... I'm not joking.

288
00:09:01,529 --> 00:09:03,068
Do you remember that? It was over 20 years ago.

289
00:09:03,069 --> 00:09:04,698
You ruined my relationship with someone I liked.

290
00:09:04,699 --> 00:09:06,368
I'm still single because of you.

291
00:09:06,369 --> 00:09:09,878
- Right. You still remember that?
- I'm not joking.

292
00:09:09,879 --> 00:09:11,539
It's been over 20 years since then, right?

293
00:09:12,009 --> 00:09:13,708
- It's been almost 20 years.
- Many years ago...

294
00:09:13,709 --> 00:09:15,148
- It was 2005, I think.
- He's laughing about it.

295
00:09:15,149 --> 00:09:16,278
It's a true story. And I'm not joking.

296
00:09:16,279 --> 00:09:17,348
One day, he came over to my house.

297
00:09:17,349 --> 00:09:19,488
There was one of my juniors I was interested in.

298
00:09:19,489 --> 00:09:20,748
- I told him about her.
- That's right.

299
00:09:20,749 --> 00:09:22,688
He offered advice. It was April Fool's Day.

300
00:09:22,689 --> 00:09:24,188
- Oh, that's right.
- He told me...

301
00:09:24,189 --> 00:09:25,959
to text her. I asked him what I should say.

302
00:09:26,229 --> 00:09:27,229
He told me to write an acrostic poem with "April Fool's Day."

303
00:09:27,230 --> 00:09:29,159
"If I love you,"

304
00:09:29,529 --> 00:09:32,028
"would we become a couple? You'd never say yes."

305
00:09:32,029 --> 00:09:33,729
He told me to send the message, but I said I couldn't do it.

306
00:09:33,869 --> 00:09:35,638
He said that if she said yes, I'd go out with her,

307
00:09:35,639 --> 00:09:37,568
and if she said no, I should say it was a prank.

308
00:09:37,569 --> 00:09:38,969
- That's how it all started.
- To read the message vertically.

309
00:09:39,069 --> 00:09:40,908
- Vertically?
- We could do it with 2G phones.

310
00:09:40,909 --> 00:09:42,038
- Reading the initial letters.
- It was trending back then.

311
00:09:42,039 --> 00:09:43,809
I was convinced and sent her the message.

312
00:09:44,409 --> 00:09:45,709
She hasn't called me ever since.

313
00:09:47,179 --> 00:09:48,249
Until now.

314
00:09:48,979 --> 00:09:50,649
It's a true story.

315
00:09:50,979 --> 00:09:52,388
He's so good at telling a story.

316
00:09:52,389 --> 00:09:55,048
It's true. It'd rather be better if she had replied,

317
00:09:55,049 --> 00:09:56,289
"What are you doing right now?"

318
00:09:56,689 --> 00:09:58,858
Then I would've given up on her.

319
00:09:58,859 --> 00:10:00,488
- But she didn't reply.
- She ignored his calls too.

320
00:10:00,489 --> 00:10:01,859
But Jang Hoon, do you think...

321
00:10:02,359 --> 00:10:04,358
- that was the only reason?
- Only because of that?

322
00:10:04,359 --> 00:10:06,828
- She would've ghosted you anyway.
- That's true.

323
00:10:06,829 --> 00:10:08,028
But she'll call him when she watches this.

324
00:10:08,029 --> 00:10:10,268
Jang Hoon, that's all in the past now.

325
00:10:10,269 --> 00:10:12,708
Why don't you show off your kicks and bring me what you prepared?

326
00:10:12,709 --> 00:10:13,908
Right. I should do that.

327
00:10:13,909 --> 00:10:15,479
We haven't seen his kicks in a long while.

328
00:10:15,879 --> 00:10:17,138
- He's so cool.
- Jang Hoon and...

329
00:10:17,139 --> 00:10:18,139
Shall I kick while moving?

330
00:10:18,140 --> 00:10:22,449
(Jang Hoon's signature move, the fiery fly kick)

331
00:10:22,619 --> 00:10:24,379
- Good to see you again, my friend.
- Good to see you too.

332
00:10:25,019 --> 00:10:26,019
(Impressed)

333
00:10:27,819 --> 00:10:28,959
Show us your kick!

334
00:10:29,689 --> 00:10:31,219
Now please sit down.

335
00:10:32,259 --> 00:10:34,629
The transfer form to Men on a Mission.

336
00:10:34,729 --> 00:10:39,128
- We'll check out their nicknames.
- Their nicknames?

337
00:10:39,129 --> 00:10:41,998
- Jadu wrote, "Quirky Singer."
- That's right.

338
00:10:41,999 --> 00:10:43,568
- Yes, I used to be called that.
- She debuted as a quirky singer.

339
00:10:43,569 --> 00:10:45,738
- It was sensational.
- Indeed.

340
00:10:45,739 --> 00:10:46,739
I was in high school back then.

341
00:10:46,740 --> 00:10:47,968
- I did so many strange things.
- There was a rumor...

342
00:10:47,969 --> 00:10:50,708
- that she was PSY's younger sister.
- Oh, right.

343
00:10:50,709 --> 00:10:52,679
I see that she had that fashion style before Crayon Pop.

344
00:10:52,779 --> 00:10:54,848
Actually, I didn't want to become a quirky singer.

345
00:10:54,849 --> 00:10:56,278
I was going to be a member of a rock band.

346
00:10:56,279 --> 00:10:58,279
- But I couldn't.
- Really?

347
00:10:58,349 --> 00:11:00,018
People saw my performances...

348
00:11:00,019 --> 00:11:02,419
and started to call me quirky,

349
00:11:02,559 --> 00:11:04,419
which put pressure on me.

350
00:11:04,519 --> 00:11:06,028
I was pressured to do unusual things...

351
00:11:06,029 --> 00:11:08,328
and maintain the quirky image.

352
00:11:08,329 --> 00:11:11,929
So I styled myself in a way that no other singers would do...

353
00:11:12,029 --> 00:11:13,828
when they performed on stage.

354
00:11:13,829 --> 00:11:15,199
That's why I wore unique glasses.

355
00:11:15,329 --> 00:11:16,668
I tried everything.

356
00:11:16,669 --> 00:11:17,898
But Jadu, before you made your debut,

357
00:11:17,899 --> 00:11:20,039
you must've heard about the concept of your group's music and style.

358
00:11:20,239 --> 00:11:22,439
- That's not true.
- No other bands had a fruit name.

359
00:11:22,509 --> 00:11:24,709
- Right.
- How did you feel about the name?

360
00:11:24,839 --> 00:11:28,608
You see, The Jadu wasn't a well-planned project.

361
00:11:28,609 --> 00:11:29,848
It's because The Jadu was...

362
00:11:29,849 --> 00:11:33,288
I used to be a rock singer who performed at Hongdae.

363
00:11:33,289 --> 00:11:35,758
- That's right.
- I often ate ramyeon.

364
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:38,759
We thought we'd debut as a rock band. We had a guitarist.

365
00:11:38,859 --> 00:11:40,428
- And Kangdu was a bassist.
- That's right.

366
00:11:40,429 --> 00:11:42,499
- Kangdu was a bassist.
- We joined the agency as a band.

367
00:11:42,599 --> 00:11:44,599
But right before our debut, the guitarist...

368
00:11:44,729 --> 00:11:46,529
left the band refusing to do that style of music.

369
00:11:46,799 --> 00:11:47,898
- The guitarist left the band.
- The rock spirit.

370
00:11:47,899 --> 00:11:49,068
- What style of music do you mean?
- Rock and roll.

371
00:11:49,069 --> 00:11:50,468
- Like K-pop songs.
- What kind of music?

372
00:11:50,469 --> 00:11:53,169
Compared to the songs we made, the songs we received...

373
00:11:53,309 --> 00:11:56,009
- were too popular.
- For a rock band.

374
00:11:56,209 --> 00:11:59,508
So the guitarist quit, and the two of us were left.

375
00:11:59,509 --> 00:12:00,949
- What's the name of the guitarist?
- We were...

376
00:12:01,349 --> 00:12:03,148
- I can't reveal the name.
- Is it Kim Tae Won?

377
00:12:03,149 --> 00:12:04,949
Yes. I mean, no. It's not him.

378
00:12:05,749 --> 00:12:07,388
- Oh, I see.
- He left your band?

379
00:12:07,389 --> 00:12:08,619
The guitarist wasn't around his age.

380
00:12:08,789 --> 00:12:10,619
- He was a member of The Jadu?
- As far as I know...

381
00:12:11,519 --> 00:12:13,588
- The guitarist wasn't that old.
- That was good timing.

382
00:12:13,589 --> 00:12:16,659
- No, that's not the case.
- So that's what happened.

383
00:12:16,829 --> 00:12:18,329
- I used to go by Ddalgi.
- So Tae Won worked with her.

384
00:12:18,529 --> 00:12:19,568
- I didn't know that.
- I said that wasn't the case.

385
00:12:19,569 --> 00:12:21,298
Tae Won is a great guitarist.

386
00:12:21,299 --> 00:12:23,339
- He's not the one.
- Don't look down on Tae Won.

387
00:12:23,599 --> 00:12:25,068
- The guitarist wasn't that old.
- Then Jadu...

388
00:12:25,069 --> 00:12:27,568
- So Tae Won was their guitarist?
- That's right.

389
00:12:27,569 --> 00:12:28,808
- Did Tae Won...
- You should have denied it.

390
00:12:28,809 --> 00:12:30,839
Did Tae Won have long hair back then as well?

391
00:12:31,009 --> 00:12:33,148
- I used to go by Ddalgi.
- Ddalgi?

392
00:12:33,149 --> 00:12:35,548
- I was Ddalgi back then.
- It wasn't Jadu?

393
00:12:35,549 --> 00:12:37,118
My alias was Ddalgi when I was a member of a rock band.

394
00:12:37,119 --> 00:12:39,818
- So the guitarist left the band.
- Then why did you change your name?

395
00:12:39,819 --> 00:12:42,088
"Ddalgi" as in "strawberry" didn't seem like a good name.

396
00:12:42,089 --> 00:12:44,188
As there was a song called "Strawberry..."

397
00:12:44,189 --> 00:12:46,458
- It was a common name.
- I like strawberries

398
00:12:46,459 --> 00:12:49,228
- The song by Pippi Band.
- I needed an uncommon fruit name.

399
00:12:49,229 --> 00:12:51,829
- Oh, I see.
- Like apple, peach, and cherry.

400
00:12:51,899 --> 00:12:52,869
When someone came up with "cherry,"

401
00:12:52,870 --> 00:12:54,868
we thought it was too pretty for me. So we thought of a less pretty one.

402
00:12:54,869 --> 00:12:57,468
We thought of a less pretty, red, round fruit,

403
00:12:57,469 --> 00:12:59,938
- and we picked "jadu" as in "plum."
- But plums are pretty too.

404
00:12:59,939 --> 00:13:02,838
- Plums are pretty.
- You performed in a lying position.

405
00:13:02,839 --> 00:13:04,638
I wasn't lying down. I fell down.

406
00:13:04,639 --> 00:13:07,379
- Really?
- I performed unconventionally...

407
00:13:07,549 --> 00:13:10,949
because I had no desire to become successful.

408
00:13:11,179 --> 00:13:14,218
Because I wanted to do rock music, but I became a pop singer.

409
00:13:14,219 --> 00:13:17,318
So I didn't want my song to be a top-ranking song.

410
00:13:17,319 --> 00:13:19,288
I didn't want to perform the song very well.

411
00:13:19,289 --> 00:13:20,988
I didn't want to do a great job on stage...

412
00:13:20,989 --> 00:13:22,558
- and impress people.
- But that made the song popular.

413
00:13:22,559 --> 00:13:24,429
- I didn't want any of those.
- You hoped the song would flop.

414
00:13:24,529 --> 00:13:25,868
- Right. Things... Yes.
- Things go well when you think so.

415
00:13:25,869 --> 00:13:27,068
- It's because...
- What was your debut song?

416
00:13:27,069 --> 00:13:28,198
- "Good Bye."
- Oh, "Good Bye."

417
00:13:28,199 --> 00:13:29,638
- All this time - All this time

418
00:13:29,639 --> 00:13:30,738
- That's how the song starts.
- It became a big hit.

419
00:13:30,739 --> 00:13:34,069
I heard the managers talk together before I went on to the stage.

420
00:13:34,439 --> 00:13:35,909
"She's gone too far."

421
00:13:36,039 --> 00:13:38,238
"It's too fast. It's too much. She's gone too far."

422
00:13:38,239 --> 00:13:40,079
I heard these comments.

423
00:13:40,249 --> 00:13:43,318
And they motivated me when I wasn't so enthusiastic.

424
00:13:43,319 --> 00:13:46,089
"I've gone too far? I'll show you what it's like when I go too far."

425
00:13:46,249 --> 00:13:47,848
The agency didn't give me any directions.

426
00:13:47,849 --> 00:13:49,318
They told me to do as I wanted.

427
00:13:49,319 --> 00:13:50,418
"You're not a good dancer, right?"

428
00:13:50,419 --> 00:13:52,328
"Just do whatever you want on stage." That's what they said.

429
00:13:52,329 --> 00:13:53,828
- That's what rock music is about.
- So I thought, "I hope it flops."

430
00:13:53,829 --> 00:13:56,058
"Whatever. I don't care." And I went up on the stage.

431
00:13:56,059 --> 00:13:57,258
- Even in my first performance...
- You literally lied down.

432
00:13:57,259 --> 00:13:59,969
No, I fell down. Anyway, I'm bad at dancing.

433
00:14:00,129 --> 00:14:01,868
- You said you fell down.
- So I just let myself go...

434
00:14:01,869 --> 00:14:03,168
- Isn't that a lie?
- while lying down on the floor.

435
00:14:03,169 --> 00:14:06,738
Right after our first performance, we got cast for so many shows.

436
00:14:06,739 --> 00:14:08,708
- What year was that?
- It was February, 2001.

437
00:14:08,709 --> 00:14:11,708
- Do you have a new nickname now?
- It became a big hit...

438
00:14:11,709 --> 00:14:13,948
- Other than "Quirky Singer."
- These days,

439
00:14:13,949 --> 00:14:15,248
I'm called Auntie Gimbap.

440
00:14:15,249 --> 00:14:17,048
- You're called Auntie Gimbap?
- Of course.

441
00:14:17,049 --> 00:14:19,388
- She looks too young to be an aunt.
- I still sing that song.

442
00:14:19,389 --> 00:14:21,048
- Please sing the song for us.
- Shall I?

443
00:14:21,049 --> 00:14:23,419
(Roll it well)

444
00:14:23,519 --> 00:14:26,588
(Press it well)

445
00:14:26,589 --> 00:14:31,029
(Just like rice sticks to dried laver)

446
00:14:31,129 --> 00:14:33,769
(I want to be glued to you)

447
00:14:34,169 --> 00:14:35,468
She has so many great songs.

448
00:14:35,469 --> 00:14:36,968
"Gimbap," "Good Bye,"

449
00:14:36,969 --> 00:14:39,639
"We Need To Talk," and "Destiny." She has a lot of hit songs.

450
00:14:39,769 --> 00:14:41,338
There are a few singers whose voices are...

451
00:14:41,339 --> 00:14:42,879
- like their fingerprints.
- That's right.

452
00:14:43,039 --> 00:14:44,839
- And Jadu is one of them.
- I can't hide it.

453
00:14:44,909 --> 00:14:46,478
No matter how many years go by,

454
00:14:46,479 --> 00:14:48,749
- if she just sings a few bars, - There's no other like her.

455
00:14:49,319 --> 00:14:50,978
- "That's Jadu's voice."
- people would recognize her voice.

456
00:14:50,979 --> 00:14:53,248
- All three of them...
- Her voice gives you chills.

457
00:14:53,249 --> 00:14:55,918
- have unique voices.
- Gi Seong's version must be good.

458
00:14:55,919 --> 00:14:58,958
- Sing it with your rusty voice.
- Roll

459
00:14:58,959 --> 00:15:00,988
(Roll it well)

460
00:15:00,989 --> 00:15:02,599
It's like there's only spinach in gimbap.

461
00:15:03,159 --> 00:15:04,658
It's as if gimbap smells fishy.

462
00:15:04,659 --> 00:15:07,328
(Not to let gimbap stick to each other)

463
00:15:07,329 --> 00:15:09,028
It's like gimbap that smells fishy.

464
00:15:09,029 --> 00:15:10,769
(Roll it well)

465
00:15:11,769 --> 00:15:12,968
He sang it in his own style.

466
00:15:12,969 --> 00:15:14,169
- He changed the lyrics too.
- Exactly.

467
00:15:14,269 --> 00:15:16,909
- That's right.
- Gimbap smells fishy?

468
00:15:17,009 --> 00:15:18,178
I really like your version of the song.

469
00:15:18,179 --> 00:15:19,308
- Now...
- It was better than the original.

470
00:15:19,309 --> 00:15:21,208
- Gimbap that smells fishy.
- "Let's make soju-beer cocktail."

471
00:15:21,209 --> 00:15:23,048
- Jang Hoon should sing it too.
- Jang Hoon's version of "Gimbap?"

472
00:15:23,049 --> 00:15:24,518
- I'll do that.
- Sing it just once.

473
