00:33:40,949 --> 00:33:42,748
- When did your voice change?
- The prime days.

970
00:33:42,749 --> 00:33:44,278
- My voice?
- We talked about the prime days.

971
00:33:44,279 --> 00:33:46,178
- Let's talk about voice changes.
- When did it change?

972
00:33:46,179 --> 00:33:47,688
- How old were you?
- The puberty voice change.

973
00:33:47,689 --> 00:33:49,219
Ninth grade!

974
00:33:49,449 --> 00:33:51,088
(Jang Hoon's voice changed in 9th grade!)

975
00:33:51,089 --> 00:33:53,389
- Ninth grade.
- Ninth grade.

976
00:33:53,829 --> 00:33:55,358
- That's crazy.
- Ninth grade.

977
00:33:55,359 --> 00:33:57,358
- It changed in ninth grade.
- Okay.

978
00:33:57,359 --> 00:33:58,359
I became possessed.

979
00:33:58,360 --> 00:33:59,658
I became possessed.

980
00:33:59,659 --> 00:34:01,728
You're really funny.

981
00:34:01,729 --> 00:34:04,368
- Let's go, Hee Chul.
- How did you live without me?

982
00:34:04,369 --> 00:34:05,438
I can't live without you.

983
00:34:05,439 --> 00:34:06,439
- Seriously.
- Goodness.

984
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:08,008
I can't live without Seo Jang Hoon and Kim Jang Hoon.

985
00:34:08,009 --> 00:34:09,368
You're enemies with Jang Hoon.

986
00:34:09,369 --> 00:34:11,679
- I really like the name Jang Hoon.
- That's true.

987
00:34:12,379 --> 00:34:13,379
I can't live without Jang Hoon.

988
00:34:13,380 --> 00:34:14,848
- Jang Hoon...
- Now,

989
00:34:14,849 --> 00:34:16,478
for the prime days, Gi Seong wrote...

990
00:34:16,479 --> 00:34:18,878
- "Don't call me cowardly."
- That's right.

991
00:34:18,879 --> 00:34:20,418
(Don't call me)

992
00:34:20,419 --> 00:34:22,188
(cowardly)

993
00:34:22,189 --> 00:34:25,588
(Even if I wander through the filthy back alleys)

994
00:34:25,589 --> 00:34:27,728
- It's a national pop song.
- A national pop song.

995
00:34:27,729 --> 00:34:28,958
- It's a really great song.
- "Piano."

996
00:34:28,959 --> 00:34:32,499
I just remember it when I hear the music.

997
00:34:32,899 --> 00:34:35,869
(A song from the 3rd album, soundtrack of "Piano")

998
00:34:36,499 --> 00:34:40,639
(The pure macho energy and his rough voice was the highlight.)

999
00:34:40,709 --> 00:34:42,608
Why did you almost not get to sing this song?

1000
00:34:42,609 --> 00:34:43,778
- Why?
- I heard you almost got rejected...

1001
00:34:43,779 --> 00:34:45,478
- because of your skills.
- That's...

1002
00:34:45,479 --> 00:34:47,308
After releasing the third album,

1003
00:34:47,309 --> 00:34:50,278
we were promoting "GoGo."

1004
00:34:50,279 --> 00:34:51,648
- Right.
- The song...

1005
00:34:51,649 --> 00:34:53,849
entered the top ten.

1006
00:34:55,119 --> 00:35:00,859
(An intense, upbeat song loved by the partygoers of that time)

1007
00:35:01,089 --> 00:35:04,158
- Around then, the team...
- That's right.

1008
00:35:04,159 --> 00:35:06,458
of drama "Piano" asked Can to sing the soundtrack.

1009
00:35:06,459 --> 00:35:07,799
So we decided to release two albums.

1010
00:35:08,069 --> 00:35:10,198
We noticed that the casts of the drama were amazing.

1011
00:35:10,199 --> 00:35:12,738
- Right. There was Zo In Sung.
- Yes. Zo In Sung,

1012
00:35:12,739 --> 00:35:14,208
- Go Soo.
- Go Soo,

1013
00:35:14,209 --> 00:35:16,168
- Kim Ha Neul.
- and Kim Ha Neul.

1014
00:35:16,169 --> 00:35:17,738
We thought it would do well...

1015
00:35:17,739 --> 00:35:19,379
and put in a lot of effort.

1016
00:35:19,679 --> 00:35:21,348
We recorded the song for many hours and sent it,

1017
00:35:21,349 --> 00:35:22,908
but it got rejected right away.

1018
00:35:22,909 --> 00:35:24,318
They said it didn't feel right.

1019
00:35:24,319 --> 00:35:25,918
I was so frustrated...

1020
00:35:25,919 --> 00:35:27,388
because we were promoting "GoGo,"

1021
00:35:27,389 --> 00:35:29,118
and we had our hit songs as well.

1022
00:35:29,119 --> 00:35:30,288
I wasn't sure if we really had to sing that song.

1023
00:35:30,289 --> 00:35:33,218
Actually, when the demo song came, it sounded like...

1024
00:35:33,219 --> 00:35:35,289
(Demo version)

1025
00:35:35,489 --> 00:35:38,259
- It sounded like a trot song.
- The original song.

1026
00:35:38,629 --> 00:35:41,569
I was so annoyed, so I just roughly sang it in one go.

1027
00:35:42,329 --> 00:35:43,499
I sang it without effort and sent it to them,

1028
00:35:43,799 --> 00:35:45,068
and they said, "That's right. This is how you should sing."

1029
00:35:45,069 --> 00:35:46,698
- It's like Jadu's case.
- Yes.

1030
00:35:46,699 --> 00:35:48,968
There are times when putting so much effort doesn't work.

1031
00:35:48,969 --> 00:35:51,978
- Right. I should relax.
- It wasn't bad,

1032
00:35:51,979 --> 00:35:54,608
but it wasn't that great to be sung with so much effort.

1033
00:35:54,609 --> 00:35:56,148
So I just sang it without effort.

1034
00:35:56,149 --> 00:35:57,548
- "It's so nice."
- They said, "This is how..."

1035
00:35:57,549 --> 00:35:58,949
"a true man's voice should be."

1036
00:35:59,679 --> 00:36:01,188
That's how you secured this song,

1037
00:36:01,189 --> 00:36:02,448
but you lost...

1038
00:36:02,449 --> 00:36:03,718
- another great hit song.
- So,

1039
00:36:03,719 --> 00:36:05,458
- we were promoting this song, - What happened?

1040
00:36:05,459 --> 00:36:07,828
- and the World Cup began.
- It began.

1041
00:36:07,829 --> 00:36:10,629
We were asked to sing a cheer song.

1042
00:36:11,059 --> 00:36:12,098
It was "Oh Fighting Korea."

1043
00:36:12,099 --> 00:36:13,258
- "Oh Fighting..."
- It suits you well.

1044
00:36:13,259 --> 00:36:14,268
("Oh Fighting Korea" by YB)

1045
00:36:14,269 --> 00:36:17,069
(The 2002 World Cup semifinal miracle)

1046
00:36:17,539 --> 00:36:21,309
(The anthem set the hearts of 47 million Red Devils on fire.)

1047
00:36:21,769 --> 00:36:24,938
(The band became a legend after that.)

1048
00:36:24,939 --> 00:36:26,538
- YB.
- For us,

1049
00:36:26,539 --> 00:36:28,648
it was before the World Cup.

1050
00:36:28,649 --> 00:36:31,848
The whole world was talking about Brazil or Germany...

1051
00:36:31,849 --> 00:36:34,619
as the winning candidates.

1052
00:36:34,919 --> 00:36:37,058
So we declined the offer.

1053
00:36:37,059 --> 00:36:39,958
We said we were promoting "Spring Days of My Life,"

1054
00:36:39,959 --> 00:36:42,029
so we were very busy.

1055
00:36:42,329 --> 00:36:43,929
But who knew we'd advance to the semifinals?

1056
00:36:44,159 --> 00:36:46,829
So YB became very famous,

1057
00:36:47,329 --> 00:36:50,998
and in 2002, Can and YB...

1058
00:36:50,999 --> 00:36:53,268
- Right. YB was...
- performed across the country.

1059
00:36:53,269 --> 00:36:54,438
Right.

1060
00:36:54,439 --> 00:36:55,969
That was really cool.

1061
00:36:56,639 --> 00:36:58,208
Could you sing a little bit of "Oh Fighting Korea?"

1062
00:36:58,209 --> 00:37:00,908
(Oh, victory, Korea)

1063
00:37:00,909 --> 00:37:02,779
- It suits you well.
- It suits you.

1064
00:37:03,249 --> 00:37:08,019
(Oh Fighting Korea macho version)

1065
00:37:08,249 --> 00:37:10,489
(Ole ole)

1066
00:37:10,689 --> 00:37:11,958
It doesn't have that original taste for sure.

1067
00:37:11,959 --> 00:37:14,959
- Jang Hoon would sing it well too.
- Hee Chul.

1068
00:37:15,159 --> 00:37:16,288
Hee Chul.

1069
00:37:16,289 --> 00:37:17,758
How would Jang Hoon sing it?

1070
00:37:17,759 --> 00:37:20,599
(Oh, victory, Korea, kick)

1071
00:37:20,769 --> 00:37:21,769
(He's thrilled.)

1072
00:37:22,129 --> 00:37:23,628
It could do great.

1073
00:37:23,629 --> 00:37:24,639
He really likes it.

1074
00:37:24,939 --> 00:37:26,798
It grows on you the more you see it.

1075
00:37:26,799 --> 00:37:28,708
- It grows on you.
- You're really great.

1076
00:37:28,709 --> 00:37:30,138
I really love Kim Jang Hoon and Seo Jang Hoon.

1077
00:37:30,139 --> 00:37:31,778
- Okay.
- He's really good.

1078
00:37:31,779 --> 00:37:33,808
Was hiding your age...

1079
00:37:33,809 --> 00:37:35,748
your own decision,

1080
00:37:35,749 --> 00:37:38,018
or did your company tell you to do it?

1081
00:37:38,019 --> 00:37:39,149
You hid your age at first, right?

1082
00:37:39,519 --> 00:37:41,088
- Did you lie about your age?
- Not at first.

1083
00:37:41,089 --> 00:37:42,618
You were born in 1973, right?

1084
00:37:42,619 --> 00:37:44,018
- In 1972.
- In 1972.

1085
00:37:44,019 --> 00:37:45,618
- What age did you say you were?
- I said I was born in 1974.

1086
00:37:45,619 --> 00:37:48,528
I just realized Gi Seong was born in 1972.

1087
00:37:48,529 --> 00:37:50,058
- Really?
- You thought he was younger.

1088
00:37:50,059 --> 00:37:51,798
- I...
- I didn't know you were there.

1089
00:37:51,799 --> 00:37:53,428
I sometimes saw him at events.

1090
00:37:53,429 --> 00:37:54,568
You were there.

1091
00:37:54,569 --> 00:37:56,368
Somewhere between "Sang Min..."

1092
00:37:56,369 --> 00:37:58,668
and "Mr. Sang Min."

1093
00:37:58,669 --> 00:38:01,139
He said, "You're here, Sang Min."

1094
00:38:01,569 --> 00:38:03,208
I thought, "He'd be younger than me."

1095
00:38:03,209 --> 00:38:05,438
- Right. He'd be a year younger.
- Yes.

1096
00:38:05,439 --> 00:38:07,278
- It was awkward.
- "Why does he talk like that?"

1097
00:38:07,279 --> 00:38:08,708
- If we maybe had a drink, - I just greeted him...

1098
00:38:08,709 --> 00:38:10,419
- like this.
- we could've introduced ourselves.

1099
00:38:10,649 --> 00:38:12,978
I saw Sang Min all the time,

1100
00:38:12,979 --> 00:38:14,218
- but only on shows.
- Are you older than him?

1101
00:38:14,219 --> 00:38:16,349
Yes. I only saw him on shows.

1102
00:38:17,019 --> 00:38:18,988
We kept meeting on shows and just left.

1103
00:38:18,989 --> 00:38:20,488
We had no chance to introduce ourselves.

1104
00:38:20,489 --> 00:38:21,528
- I knew that today.
- Yes.

1105
00:38:21,529 --> 00:38:23,528
Did you just get here, Sang Min, or have you always been here?

1106
00:38:23,529 --> 00:38:25,298
I've been here since earlier.

1107
00:38:25,299 --> 00:38:27,298
It's hard to see him from there because of Ho Dong.

1108
00:38:27,299 --> 00:38:29,129
It's hard to see him from there.

1109
00:38:29,369 --> 00:38:32,269
I met Jang Hoon on another show long ago.

1110
00:38:32,739 --> 00:38:34,339
You had a huge panic attack back then,

1111
00:38:34,509 --> 00:38:36,309
so I'm trying not to speak to you.

1112
00:38:36,739 --> 00:38:38,778
- Jang Hoon did?
- Jang Hoon had a panic attack?

1113
00:38:38,779 --> 00:38:40,908
When he was asked a question, he didn't answer it,

1114
00:38:40,909 --> 00:38:42,378
but talked about something else instead.

1115
00:38:42,379 --> 00:38:43,408
Jang Hoon did that?

1116
00:38:43,409 --> 00:38:45,748
- You don't listen when you get old.
- Up to three times,

1117
00:38:45,749 --> 00:38:47,389
that's okay,

1118
00:38:47,789 --> 00:38:50,819
- but he repeated that 20 times.
- It wasn't 20 times.

1119
00:38:51,189 --> 00:38:52,759
- That's nonsense.
- So I lost it.

1120
00:38:53,089 --> 00:38:54,828
I screamed at him to just answer my questions...

1121
00:38:54,829 --> 00:38:57,298
and not say anything else.

1122
00:38:57,299 --> 00:38:58,429
- Really?
- Yes.

1123
00:38:58,859 --> 00:39:00,699
Because he has panic disorder too.

1124
00:39:01,199 --> 00:39:02,998
- They both do.
- Jang Hoon struggles with it too.

1125
00:39:02,999 --> 00:39:04,638
- I do.
- They both do.

1126
00:39:04,639 --> 00:39:05,998
Panic disorder versus panic disorder.

1127
00:39:05,999 --> 00:39:07,568
- It's different.
- Panic disorder...

1128
00:39:07,569 --> 00:39:08,768
versus panic disorder.

1129
00:39:08,769 --> 00:39:10,679
I didn't want to lose to him when it came to panic attacks.

1130
00:39:11,739 --> 00:39:12,838
Wait a minute.

1131
00:39:12,839 --> 00:39:14,078
- To see who gets it first?
- I mean...

1132
00:39:14,079 --> 00:39:15,809
- That's so weird.
- Why would you battle that?

1133
00:39:15,879 --> 00:39:17,178
- I'm getting a panic attack.
- Since we both have it,

1134
00:39:17,179 --> 00:39:19,378
I didn't want to lose against him,

1135
00:39:19,379 --> 00:39:21,388
- That's so weird.
- so I endured and put him in panic.

1136
00:39:21,389 --> 00:39:22,719
- By saying the wrong things?
- That's it.

1137
00:39:23,719 --> 00:39:26,088
When you have a panic attack, you become speechless.

1138
00:39:26,089 --> 00:39:27,858
- I know.
- I guess I can now say that...

1139
00:39:27,859 --> 00:39:29,329
Gi Seong is older than me.

1140
00:39:29,489 --> 00:39:31,498
- I didn't lie...
- He cut two years.

1141
00:39:31,499 --> 00:39:32,799
about my age on purpose.

1142
00:39:32,999 --> 00:39:34,399
- I had my debut in 1993.
- Yes.

1143
00:39:34,929 --> 00:39:36,498
You were a late starter, right?

1144
00:39:36,499 --> 00:39:38,768
I gained popularity late when I was in Can.

1145
00:39:38,769 --> 00:39:41,638
- I was almost 30 years old then.
- That's just like me.

1146
00:39:41,639 --> 00:39:43,568
And around then, Click-B had their debut,

1147
00:39:43,569 --> 00:39:45,879
and they were 18 to 19.

1148
00:39:46,479 --> 00:39:49,809
- Kyung Hoon was also 20 years old.
- Yes.

1149
00:39:49,949 --> 00:39:52,819
I seemed too old to be on television.

1150
00:39:53,019 --> 00:39:55,788
Even if I cut two years,

1151
00:39:55,789 --> 00:39:57,718
- I was still over 25.
- Others were 18.

1152
00:39:57,719 --> 00:39:59,418
He was way over 30...

1153
00:39:59,419 --> 00:40:01,459
and nearing 40, so he had to fake his age.

1154
00:40:01,729 --> 00:40:04,199
When I debuted, I just said that I was 29 years old,

1155
00:40:04,429 --> 00:40:06,859
but we didn't have phones back then.

1156
00:40:07,229 --> 00:40:08,428
"We didn't have phones."

1157
00:40:08,429 --> 00:40:09,898
It was so long ago, when I was young.

1158
00:40:09,899 --> 00:40:12,239
So my first two albums flopped,

1159
00:40:12,599 --> 00:40:14,069
and I went to the company.

1160
00:40:14,309 --> 00:40:15,668
Since my mom was having such a hard time,

1161
00:40:15,669 --> 00:40:16,968
I asked them "How can I get famous?"

1162
00:40:16,969 --> 00:40:18,138
They said, "You're 34."

1163
00:40:18,139 --> 00:40:20,378
"Isn't that too old to be a rookie singer?"

1164
00:40:20,379 --> 00:40:21,648
They told me to leave the first two albums...

1165
00:40:21,649 --> 00:40:22,749
and just start over.

1166
00:40:23,309 --> 00:40:24,479
Forget about the flopped albums,

1167
00:40:24,579 --> 00:40:25,848
- Yes.
- and start over.

1168
00:40:25,849 --> 00:40:28,388
- We had no choice back then.
- We managed to say...

1169
00:40:28,389 --> 00:40:29,818
Since it had to be in the 20s...

1170
00:40:29,819 --> 00:40:31,358
I was born in 1963, but to say that I was 29,

1171
00:40:31,359 --> 00:40:32,418
we cut 5 years to 1968.

1172
00:40:32,419 --> 00:40:34,888
- I looked younger than my age.
- He was such a handsome guy.

1173
00:40:34,889 --> 00:40:37,698
It's because you had a strong sense of responsibility as a son...

1174
00:40:37,699 --> 00:40:40,499
and wanted to become a famous singer.

1175
00:40:41,369 --> 00:40:45,298
Then there must have been fellow singers...

1176
00:40:45,299 --> 00:40:47,369
who thought they were older than you.

1177
00:40:47,709 --> 00:40:49,909
Back then, all the singers lied about their age.

1178
00:40:50,779 --> 00:40:52,338
- They all had no idea.
- So then...

1179
00:40:52,339 --> 00:40:55,078
Jae Hoon of Country Kko Kko showed up,

1180
00:40:55,079 --> 00:40:56,478
and his profile said that he was my age.

1181
00:40:56,479 --> 00:40:58,079
- My profile said 1974, - Yes.

1182
00:40:58,249 --> 00:40:59,478
but I was born in 1972.

1183
00:40:59,479 --> 00:41:01,548
- His profile said 1972.
- Jae Hoon?

1184
00:41:01,549 --> 00:41:04,089
I greeted him,

1185
00:41:04,589 --> 00:41:06,789
but he was actually born in 1968, and he had cut 4 years.

1186
00:41:08,829 --> 00:41:11,558
It was because back then, they didn't like it...

1187
00:41:11,559 --> 00:41:13,799
- when rookies were old.
- That's right.

1188
00:41:14,369 --> 00:41:16,069
- It was like that.
- You had to check.

1189
00:41:16,529 --> 00:41:18,898
Since we're talking about Jang Hoon, his peak time was...

1190
00:41:18,899 --> 00:41:20,709
during "If Like Me."

1191
00:41:21,639 --> 00:41:22,709
Yes.

1192
00:41:23,339 --> 00:41:28,749
(An unpolished yet emotionally resonant voice)

1193
00:41:30,009 --> 00:41:35,219
(The song that made Jang Hoon a star)

1194
00:41:35,389 --> 00:41:37,419
This was your first hit song, right?

1195
00:41:37,659 --> 00:41:39,018
True.

1196
00:41:39,019 --> 00:41:40,088
- "True?"
- "True?"

1197
00:41:40,089 --> 00:41:41,558
- Isn't it "sure?"
- What year was that?

1198
00:41:41,559 --> 00:41:43,759
- True.
- What year was that, Jang Hoon?

1199
00:41:44,029 --> 00:41:45,998
It was released on February 16, 1998.

1200
00:41:45,999 --> 00:41:47,328
I had my debut on 1991.

1201
00:41:47,329 --> 00:41:49,168
I had my first album when I was 29, but I spent 7 years unknown.

1202
00:41:49,169 --> 00:41:52,398
Now that I think of it, it's not easy to have a hit song at 36.

1203
00:41:52,399 --> 00:41:53,638
- Yes.
- Sure. It's great.

1204
00:41:53,639 --> 00:41:55,268
- Of course.
- You lose popularity at that age.

1205
00:41:55,269 --> 00:41:56,439
(After "If Like Me" in 1998...)

1206
00:41:57,409 --> 00:42:01,808
(He came back with a unique masterpiece each time...)

1207
00:42:01,809 --> 00:42:05,578
(and established himself as a singer who defined the era.)

1208
00:42:05,579 --> 00:42:07,488
You wanted to become a popular,

1209
00:42:07,489 --> 00:42:09,248
well-loved singer, right?

1210
00:42:09,249 --> 00:42:10,988
My family was really well-off when I was young,

1211
00:42:10,989 --> 00:42:12,258
but then, we faced three asset seizures.

1212
00:42:12,259 --> 00:42:14,228
I don't have a father, and my mother ran a business.

1213
00:42:14,229 --> 00:42:17,188
My mother lived in a place where the monthly rent was 80 dollars,

1214
00:42:17,189 --> 00:42:21,129
and one day, I came home, and I suddenly felt really irritated.

1215
00:42:21,499 --> 00:42:23,428
I wasn't even after musical artistry,

1216
00:42:23,429 --> 00:42:24,539
so I just said, "Okay,"

1217
00:42:24,799 --> 00:42:26,069
and gave in.

1218
00:42:26,369 --> 00:42:27,669
I went back to the agency at age 30.

1219
00:42:27,909 --> 00:42:30,808
I went to the agency where Kim Hyun Shik was,

1220
00:42:30,809 --> 00:42:31,878
since I knew him since I was in high school.

1221
00:42:31,879 --> 00:42:33,179
I asked, "How can I get famous?"

1222
00:42:33,309 --> 00:42:34,708
"I need to earn money."

1223
00:42:34,709 --> 00:42:36,149
He told me to promise him three things.

1224
00:42:36,349 --> 00:42:38,078
"Don’t lose your temper and fight."

1225
00:42:38,079 --> 00:42:39,119
"Don't fight."

1226
00:42:39,249 --> 00:42:40,379
"No heavy metal."

1227
00:42:40,749 --> 00:42:42,519
It had to be a song that everyone could sing along to.

1228
00:42:42,589 --> 00:42:44,659
Lastly, "You have to be on television."

1229
00:42:45,259 --> 00:42:46,289
Three things.

1230
00:42:46,389 --> 00:42:48,588
- That was when I...
- You listened to him.

1231
00:42:48,589 --> 00:42:49,658
I did.

1232
00:42:49,659 --> 00:42:51,399
But that agency isn't into television shows.

1233
00:42:51,559 --> 00:42:53,359
They had Kim Hyun Shik, Deulgukhwa,

1234
00:42:53,629 --> 00:42:55,829
- Han Young Ae, and so on.
- SSAW, as well.

1235
00:42:55,999 --> 00:42:57,168
They mostly do stage performances.

1236
00:42:57,169 --> 00:43:00,909
They realized that Jang Hoon's face was fit for the screen.

1237
00:43:01,469 --> 00:43:03,338
- He really is handsome.
- His visuals...

1238
00:43:03,339 --> 00:43:04,978
were for the screen, for sure.

1239
00:43:04,979 --> 00:43:06,438
He had a bad temper,

1240
00:43:06,439 --> 00:43:07,678
but his face was really handsome.

1241
00:43:07,679 --> 00:43:08,948
- I was handsome back then.
- The important thing is,

1242
00:43:08,949 --> 00:43:11,718
he didn't just accept the love, but he gave it back...

1243
00:43:11,719 --> 00:43:13,118
- through donations...
- Yes.

1244
00:43:13,119 --> 00:43:14,519
to create positive influence.

1245
00:43:14,719 --> 00:43:17,588
I saw the news that you donated about 20 million dollars,

1246
00:43:17,589 --> 00:43:21,088
and you only have 30 thousand dollars in your account.

1247
00:43:21,089 --> 00:43:22,989
About Jang Hoon's marriage plans...

1248
00:43:23,459 --> 00:43:25,299
Which Jang Hoon should I ask?

1249
00:43:25,759 --> 00:43:26,898
(They are both single.)

1250
00:43:26,899 --> 00:43:27,969
Which one?

1251
00:43:28,169 --> 00:43:29,998
The staff told me to ask Jang Hoon...

1252
00:43:29,999 --> 00:43:31,398
about his marriage plans.

1253
00:43:31,399 --> 00:43:33,099
- This is for both of them.
- Is it for both?

1254
00:43:33,599 --> 00:43:34,709
Sorry, I was confused.

1255
00:43:35,069 --> 00:43:37,269
- I was confused.
- Read it again.

1256
00:43:37,439 --> 00:43:38,879
Just say that it's for both of them.

1257
00:43:39,009 --> 00:43:40,909
- Either one of you can answer.
- Jang Hoon.

1258
00:43:41,179 --> 00:43:43,078
That Jang... You go first.

1259
00:43:43,079 --> 00:43:44,148
"You go first."

1260
00:43:44,149 --> 00:43:46,478
(He passes on the shared question.)

1261
00:43:46,479 --> 00:43:47,588
Do you really have no plans...

1262
00:43:47,589 --> 00:43:48,649
- to get married?
- Right.

1263
00:43:49,019 --> 00:43:50,019
I can't.

1264
00:43:50,020 --> 00:43:51,158
Aren't you lonely?

1265
00:43:51,159 --> 00:43:52,389
- What?
- Aren't you lonely?

1266
00:43:52,659 --> 00:43:54,019
I'm not. I don't feel that.

1267
00:43:54,489 --> 00:43:57,229
I had a 5-year rest period in my 50s.

1268
00:43:57,759 --> 00:43:59,758
Self-reflection for 2 years, and COVID-19 went on for 3 years.

1269
00:43:59,759 --> 00:44:02,129
It would have been nice if they overlapped,

1270
00:44:02,369 --> 00:44:05,139
but COVID-19 hit right after my self-reflection period.

1271
00:44:05,669 --> 00:44:08,469
So I had to rest for 5 to 6 years.

1272
00:44:08,709 --> 00:44:12,439
I became a workaholic again after entering my 60s.

1273
00:44:12,879 --> 00:44:15,378
When Jang Hoon gets married,

1274
00:44:15,379 --> 00:44:17,208
- I want to host the ceremony.
- Forget it.

1275
00:44:17,209 --> 00:44:18,349
No matter which Jang Hoon it is.

1276
00:44:18,419 --> 00:44:21,248
- For me...
- They are my favorite Jang Hoons.

1277
00:44:21,249 --> 00:44:22,348
A joint wedding.

1278
00:44:22,349 --> 00:44:23,519
- That's...
- What?

1279
00:44:23,819 --> 00:44:25,019
- A joint wedding?
- It sounds good.

1280
00:44:25,719 --> 00:44:26,788
- A double Jang Hoon wedding.
- Ho Dong.

1281
00:44:26,789 --> 00:44:28,058
It sounds good.

1282
00:44:28,059 --> 00:44:29,389
- You can do that.
- Come on.

1283
00:44:29,489 --> 00:44:31,558
- You're not like this.
- You won't be as lonely.

1284
00:44:31,559 --> 00:44:34,328
Then I will sing "Last Game" as the wedding song.

1285
00:44:34,329 --> 00:44:35,329
(Kim Hee Chul, Wedding song, I will sing "Last Game.")

1286
00:44:35,699 --> 00:44:38,639
(Groom No.1 lost his temper on a happy day.)

1287
00:44:38,769 --> 00:44:40,269
That was so...

1288
00:44:40,499 --> 00:44:43,469
Jadu wrote "Roll it well."

1289
00:44:43,609 --> 00:44:46,309
I think so. The longest-running song...

1290
00:44:46,609 --> 00:44:48,209
- was "Gimbap."
- "Gimbap."

1291
00:44:49,249 --> 00:44:52,579
(A bright and catchy melody)

1292
00:44:54,119 --> 00:44:57,818
(A witty and lovely song with lyrics that compare...)

1293
00:44:57,819 --> 00:44:59,489
(a romantic relationship to gimbap)

1294
00:44:59,619 --> 00:45:02,359
That was the concept, but did you actually like gimbap?

1295
00:45:02,689 --> 00:45:04,798
In the past, I really didn't like gimbap.

1296
00:45:04,799 --> 00:45:06,528
I hated gimbap so much that...

1297
00:45:06,529 --> 00:45:09,269
even the smell of sesame oil from it would trigger a reaction.

1298
00:45:09,529 --> 00:45:11,438
But now, I really love gimbap.

1299
00:45:11,439 --> 00:45:14,069
I attended any kind of gimbap event...

1300
00:45:14,209 --> 00:45:16,438
- or any place that had gimbap.
- Really?

1301
00:45:16,439 --> 00:45:17,538
Yes.

1302
00:45:17,539 --> 00:45:18,938
I'm sure I was closer to gimbap...

1303
00:45:18,939 --> 00:45:20,808
than any other gimbap store owner.

1304
00:45:20,809 --> 00:45:23,408
- I'm serious.
- There are many gimbap festivals.

1305
00:45:23,409 --> 00:45:24,418
- Yes.
- In each region.

1306
00:45:24,419 --> 00:45:27,148
- That's right.
- They had one in Gimcheon recently.

1307
00:45:27,149 --> 00:45:28,318
I've been attending that...

1308
00:45:28,319 --> 00:45:29,518
- since they first started.
- Really?

1309
00:45:29,519 --> 00:45:31,289
Yes, I've been attending that since the first year.

1310
00:45:31,489 --> 00:45:33,988
Gimcheon’s local specialty is plums.

1311
00:45:33,989 --> 00:45:35,388
I thought that's why they invited me.

1312
00:45:35,389 --> 00:45:36,888
- Yes.
- That's perfect.

1313
00:45:36,889 --> 00:45:38,328
I thought that was the reason.

1314
00:45:38,329 --> 00:45:40,828
But it turned out to be that the Gen Z of Gimcheon...

1315
00:45:40,829 --> 00:45:43,599
loved the festival, and my song was used as the theme song.

1316
00:45:43,799 --> 00:45:46,198
Thanks to that, I became known as the original singer...

1317
00:45:46,199 --> 00:45:48,509
of this song to the Gen Z.

1318
00:45:48,839 --> 00:45:50,639
It was their second year this year,

1319
00:45:50,769 --> 00:45:53,678
and more people showed up than the population of Gimcheon.

1320
00:45:53,679 --> 00:45:54,808
(The population is 130,000, but 150,000 people attended.)

1321
00:45:54,809 --> 00:45:57,209
And after this recording airs,

1322
00:45:57,379 --> 00:45:59,248
I’ll probably be appointed...

1323
00:45:59,249 --> 00:46:00,949
as the ambassador and honorary citizen...

1324
00:46:01,089 --> 00:46:02,988
- of Gimcheon City.
- "Honorary citizen?"

1325
00:46:02,989 --> 00:46:04,789
- Yes, thank you.
- Then...

1326
00:46:05,059 --> 00:46:07,958
- You need to answer this quickly.
- Okay.

1327
00:46:07,959 --> 00:46:09,329
Do you like plums or gimbap?

1328
00:46:09,489 --> 00:46:10,629
I like gimbap.

1329
00:46:11,359 --> 00:46:12,598
- It's true.
- Sure.

1330
00:46:12,599 --> 00:46:14,929
I like gimbap now. Gimbap saved Jadu.

1331
00:46:15,299 --> 00:46:16,398
- Sure.
- Let's listen to her song.

1332
00:46:16,399 --> 00:46:17,838
- Okay, let's go.
- Okay.

1333
00:46:17,839 --> 00:46:19,139
We need to listen to her.

1334
00:46:19,269 --> 00:46:21,069
Let's clap.

1335
00:46:21,569 --> 00:46:24,539
("Good Bye" by The Jadu)

1336
00:46:41,259 --> 00:46:42,259
(Just run!)

1337
00:46:44,959 --> 00:46:45,959
(Don't even cry!)

1338
00:46:56,369 --> 00:46:57,679
Just!

1339
00:46:58,409 --> 00:47:00,009
(It's Kangdu's part. Just!)

1340
00:47:00,439 --> 00:47:03,908
("We Need To Talk" by The Jadu)

1341
00:47:03,909 --> 00:47:05,019
It was random.

1342
00:47:13,219 --> 00:47:15,489
(The two Jang Hoons are close.)

1343
00:47:23,529 --> 00:47:28,539
(We need to talk)

1344
00:47:29,569 --> 00:47:33,239
("Gimbap" by The Jadu)

1345
00:47:50,259 --> 00:47:56,229
("I Want To Live" by The Jadu)

1346
00:48:16,389 --> 00:48:17,859
I want to live.

1347
00:48:18,059 --> 00:48:23,589
(I want to live)

1348
00:48:25,999 --> 00:48:27,868
- Her voice is still the same.
- Yes.

1349
00:48:27,869 --> 00:48:30,428
- That was awesome.
- It was so refreshing to hear.

1350
00:48:30,429 --> 00:48:32,199
- Kangdu's part was missing.
- My shoelaces are all untied.

1351
00:48:32,339 --> 00:48:35,638
- Jadu's song changed the mood.
- That was incredible.

1352
00:48:35,639 --> 00:48:38,038
Even for our friends, who were such big stars,

1353
00:48:38,039 --> 00:48:40,209
- this period inevitably came.
- Why?

1354
00:48:40,579 --> 00:48:41,779
It's a period of stagnation.

1355
00:48:42,009 --> 00:48:43,348
- This...
- They all did, not just Jang Hoon?

1356
00:48:43,349 --> 00:48:46,219
They wrote this themselves. It says, "Analyzing the reason."

1357
00:48:46,449 --> 00:48:48,488
Really, though. I think we should analyze...

1358
00:48:48,489 --> 00:48:50,649
why you guys went through periods of stagnation.

1359
00:48:50,689 --> 00:48:53,418
In my case, "Spring Days of My Life" became a huge hit...

1360
00:48:53,419 --> 00:48:55,928
and received lots of love. For about six years,

1361
00:48:55,929 --> 00:48:57,288
I only got about three hours of sleep...

1362
00:48:57,289 --> 00:48:58,659
- and worked the whole time.
- Right.

1363
00:48:58,929 --> 00:49:02,128
But then, I was so worn out. I once had a nosebleed,

1364
00:49:02,129 --> 00:49:04,229
and it wouldn't stop for an hour and a half.

1365
00:49:04,639 --> 00:49:07,909
That was the first time I missed a shoot and went to the ER.

1366
00:49:08,139 --> 00:49:10,068
It was because I was sleep deprived and under a lot of stress.

1367
00:49:10,069 --> 00:49:11,638
- You need sleep.
- So I told my agency,

1368
00:49:11,639 --> 00:49:14,548
"I want to rest. Please let me rest for a bit."

1369
00:49:14,549 --> 00:49:17,408
At the time, my schedule for the next month...

1370
00:49:17,409 --> 00:49:19,079
had about 70 or so gigs planned.

1371
00:49:19,749 --> 00:49:21,849
I told them that I wanted to stop.

1372
00:49:22,219 --> 00:49:25,219
Then, they said that I could stop, so I left the agency.

1373
00:49:25,389 --> 00:49:27,418
So I took a break for about a year,

1374
00:49:27,419 --> 00:49:29,729
and I'm not lying when I say this. People didn't recognize me.

1375
00:49:29,859 --> 00:49:31,328
- In a year?
- Yes, in a year.

1376
00:49:31,329 --> 00:49:32,598
Well, they knew it was me,

1377
00:49:32,599 --> 00:49:35,168
but all that glamorous fame...

1378
00:49:35,169 --> 00:49:36,268
totally disappeared.

1379
00:49:36,269 --> 00:49:37,968
- People forget quickly.
- Then, my songs didn't do well...

1380
00:49:37,969 --> 00:49:39,269
from that point on.

1381
00:49:39,339 --> 00:49:41,268
- You lose confidence.
- I lost confidence,

1382
00:49:41,269 --> 00:49:42,668
and as I said before,

1383
00:49:42,669 --> 00:49:44,939
I couldn't go out and eat on my own.

1384
00:49:45,409 --> 00:49:47,909
Stuff like that kept happening, and I gradually felt...

1385
00:49:48,379 --> 00:49:50,178
these things building up as stress,

1386
00:49:50,179 --> 00:49:52,549
and I started to live a secluded life.

1387
00:49:52,749 --> 00:49:55,349
That's when my period of not working began.

1388
00:49:55,449 --> 00:49:56,988
- I see.
- That was my period of stagnation.

1389
00:49:56,989 --> 00:49:58,758
There's no such thing as taking a short break.

1390
00:49:58,759 --> 00:50:00,658
These days, there are things like social media...

1391
00:50:00,659 --> 00:50:02,228
- and YouTube, so you still work.
- Right.

1392
00:50:02,229 --> 00:50:04,558
- But back then, without TV, - Those things didn't exist then.

1393
00:50:04,559 --> 00:50:06,228
- They didn't.
- you didn't have any work.

1394
00:50:06,229 --> 00:50:07,528
- There was only TV and radio.
- Right.

1395
00:50:07,529 --> 00:50:08,798
You couldn't work if they didn't call you.

1396
00:50:08,799 --> 00:50:10,468
Jadu, you didn't have a period of stagnation.

1397
00:50:10,469 --> 00:50:13,298
No, I was out of work for a very long time.

1398
00:50:13,299 --> 00:50:15,438
In my case, there were two reasons.

1399
00:50:15,439 --> 00:50:18,478
The first was that I was tricked so many times.

1400
00:50:18,479 --> 00:50:20,908
People would trick me and cause trouble all around me.

1401
00:50:20,909 --> 00:50:24,248
I wasn't capable of enduring these things...

1402
00:50:24,249 --> 00:50:25,918
or handling them.

1403
00:50:25,919 --> 00:50:28,988
Another thing, and I just thought of this recently,

1404
00:50:28,989 --> 00:50:31,558
- is that I wasn't proud of myself.
- Right.

1405
00:50:31,559 --> 00:50:33,618
I wasn't proud of myself,

1406
00:50:33,619 --> 00:50:35,959
and I was so ashamed of myself.

1407
00:50:36,059 --> 00:50:39,998
So, later on, I didn't even want to do a good job.

1408
00:50:39,999 --> 00:50:41,928
- What is being a celebrity?
- You weren't proud of yourself?

1409
00:50:41,929 --> 00:50:44,468
I had no desire to be successful at doing this,

1410
00:50:44,469 --> 00:50:46,268
so naturally, I drifted away from it.

1411
00:50:46,269 --> 00:50:49,568
I also thought that if I played music that I wanted to make,

1412
00:50:49,569 --> 00:50:51,478
- I'd be recognized by people.
- Right.

1413
00:50:51,479 --> 00:50:54,478
- Goodness, I had nowhere to go.
- Right, nowhere to go.

1414
00:50:54,479 --> 00:50:56,408
There was no one to listen.

1415
00:50:56,409 --> 00:50:59,878
So it took me a long time to face my hit songs once again.

1416
00:50:59,879 --> 00:51:01,178
- I see.
- If only you had...

1417
00:51:01,179 --> 00:51:02,448
half of Yeong Cheol's confidence.

1418
00:51:02,449 --> 00:51:04,618
He is so proud of himself.

1419
00:51:04,619 --> 00:51:07,318
- Is that true?
- That's why I envy Yeong Cheol.

1420
00:51:07,319 --> 00:51:09,028
- He's proud and loves himself.
- That's a good thing.

1421
00:51:09,029 --> 00:51:10,628
- It's a great thing.
- When we work, that's so important.

1422
00:51:10,629 --> 00:51:12,629
On the other hand, his agency is in a period of stagnation.

1423
00:51:13,929 --> 00:51:17,028
- Mystic Story is in a bad slump.
- My agency is really struggling.

1424
00:51:17,029 --> 00:51:18,268
For real. My agency hasn't been letting me...

1425
00:51:18,269 --> 00:51:19,498
- record any songs since last year.
- I know, right?

1426
00:51:19,499 --> 00:51:21,068
- You haven't had any new songs.
- If I tell them...

1427
00:51:21,069 --> 00:51:23,809
As for Jang Hoon, is it the reason we know?

1428
00:51:23,969 --> 00:51:26,078
Your worst period of stagnation.

1429
00:51:26,079 --> 00:51:28,078
My period of stagnation was so...

1430
00:51:28,079 --> 00:51:31,319
- It kept going up and down so much.
- Up and down.

1431
00:51:31,519 --> 00:51:34,378
I couldn't stand it, so I once left the country.

1432
00:51:34,379 --> 00:51:36,288
- Did you run away?
- I didn't want to be a singer.

1433
00:51:36,289 --> 00:51:38,619
I ran away once in 2003.

1434
00:51:39,059 --> 00:51:41,889
I just thought, "Let's stop." And I had three houses back then,

1435
00:51:42,089 --> 00:51:43,828
but I sold all of them.

1436
00:51:43,829 --> 00:51:46,328
I was an unknown singer before, and I became popular since 1998.

1437
00:51:46,329 --> 00:51:49,028
I didn't have any regrets, so I just left.

1438
00:51:49,029 --> 00:51:51,569
But then, I came back once I developed a panic disorder.

1439
00:51:52,039 --> 00:51:53,968
- That saved my life, in a way.
- Right.

1440
00:51:53,969 --> 00:51:55,908
I left everything behind, but I developed a panic disorder.

1441
00:51:55,909 --> 00:51:58,678
"Wouldn't this actually make me sing well?"

1442
00:51:58,679 --> 00:52:00,578
I was glad about it.

1443
00:52:00,579 --> 00:52:04,209
Unexpectedly, my emotions stayed calm.

1444
00:52:04,679 --> 00:52:06,178
Even when something big happened,

1445
00:52:06,179 --> 00:52:08,748
I was so used to running away from home and living on the streets...

1446
00:52:08,749 --> 00:52:10,548
from such a young age.

1447
00:52:10,549 --> 00:52:12,418
- "I've already been through it."
- You were unfazed.

1448
00:52:12,419 --> 00:52:15,588
